The paper proposes a memory architecture based on recursive sketching, which is a technique commonly used in artificial intelligence and machine learning. The paper also discusses the use of subspace embeddings, which are commonly used in natural language processing and computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.AI, cs.LG, and cs.NE. The paper also discusses the use of sketches to form an implicit knowledge graph, which is a concept commonly used in natural language processing and information retrieval, suggesting the sub-categories cs.CL and cs.CV as less likely but still possible.
